It is a measure of the average translational kinetic energy associated with the disordered microscopic motion of atoms and molecules. Temperature is measured in one of the three standard temperature scales: Celsius, Kelvin, and Fahrenheit. (NCI)

label: Weight
definition: The vertical force exerted by a mass as a result of gravity. (NCI)

label: No Yes Response
pref_label: CDISC SDTM Yes No Unknown or Not Applicable Response Terminology
definition: A term that is used to indicate a question with permissible values of yes/no/unknown/not applicable.

label: No
definition: The non-affirmative response to a question. (NCI)

label: Not Applicable
definition: Determination of a value is not relevant in the current context. (NCI)

label: Unknown
definition: Not known, not observed, not recorded, or refused. (NCI)

label: Yes
definition: The affirmative response to a question. (NCI)

label: Laboratory Test Code
pref_label: CDISC SDTM Laboratory Test Terminology by Code
definition: Terminology used for Laboratory Tests of the CDISC Standard Data Tabulation Model.

label: Anisocytosis
definition: A measurement of the inequality in the size of the red blood cells in a whole blood specimen.

label: Poikilocytosis
definition: A measurement of the odd-shaped erythrocytes in a whole blood specimen.

label: Total Bilirubin
definition: A measurement of the total bilirubin in a biological specimen.

label: Partial Thromboplastin Time
definition: A measurement of the length of time that it takes for clotting to occur when reagents are added to a plasma specimen. The test is partial due to the absence of tissue factor (Factor III) from the reaction mixture.

label: Plasma Glucose Measurement
definition: A measurement of the glucose in a biological specimen.

label: pH
definition: A measure of the acidity or alkalinity of a fluid on a scale of 0 to 14.

label: Erythrocyte Count
definition: A count of the total erythrocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Reticulocyte Count
definition: A count of the reticulocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Leukocyte Count
definition: A count of the leukocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Lymphocyte Count
definition: A count of the lymphocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Platelet Count
definition: A count of the platelets per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Blood Urea Nitrogen Measurement
definition: A measurement of the urea nitrogen in a blood specimen.

label: Serum Total Cholesterol Measurement
definition: A measurement of the cholesterol in a biological specimen.

label: Serum HDL Cholesterol Measurement
definition: A measurement of the high density lipoprotein cholesterol in a biological specimen.

label: Serum LDL Cholesterol Measurement
definition: A measurement of the low density lipoprotein cholesterol in a biological specimen.

label: Prothrombin Time
definition: A blood clotting measurement that evaluates the extrinsic pathway of coagulation and is expressed in units of time or percent activity.

label: Absolute Neutrophil Count
definition: A count of the neutrophils per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Albumin Measurement
definition: A measurement of the albumin protein in a biological specimen.

label: Alkaline Phosphatase Measurement
definition: A measurement of the alkaline phosphatase in a biological specimen.

label: Alanine Aminotransferase Measurement
definition: A measurement of the alanine aminotransferase in a biological specimen.

label: Amylase Measurement
definition: A measurement of the pancreatic enzyme amylase in a biological specimen.

label: Aspartate Aminotransferase Measurement
definition: A measurement of the aspartate aminotransferase in a biological specimen.

label: Bacterial Count
definition: A measurement of the bacteria in a biological specimen.

label: Total Basophil Count
definition: A count of the basophils per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Basophil To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of the basophils to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Direct Bilirubin Measurement
definition: A measurement of the conjugated or water-soluble bilirubin in a biological specimen.

label: Indirect Bilirubin Measurement
definition: A measurement of the unconjugated or non-water-soluble bilirubin in a biological specimen.

label: Blast To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of the blasts to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Calcium Measurement
definition: A measurement of the calcium in a biological specimen.

label: Creatine Kinase Measurement
definition: A measurement of the total creatine kinase in a biological specimen.

label: Creatine Kinase BB Measurement
definition: A measurement of the homozygous B-type creatine kinase in a biological specimen.

label: Creatine Kinase MB Measurement
definition: A measurement of the heterozygous MB-type creatine kinase in a biological specimen.

label: Creatine Kinase MM Measurement
definition: A measurement of the homozygous M-type creatine kinase in a biological specimen.

label: Chloride Measurement
definition: A measurement of the chloride in a biological specimen.

label: Carbon Dioxide Measurement
definition: A measurement of the carbon dioxide gas in a biological specimen.

label: Color Assessment
definition: A measurement of the color of a biological specimen.

label: Creatinine Measurement
definition: A measurement of the creatinine in a biological specimen.

label: C-Reactive Protein Measurement
definition: A measurement of the C reactive protein in a biological specimen.

label: Elliptocyte Count
definition: A count of the elliptocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Eosinophil Count
definition: A count of the eosinophils per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Eosinophil To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of the eosinophils to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Epithelial Cell Count
definition: A measurement of the epithelial cells in a biological specimen.

label: Fibrinogen Measurement
definition: A measurement of the fibrinogen in a biological specimen.

label: Hematocrit
definition: The percentage of a whole blood specimen that is composed of red blood cells (erythrocytes).

label: Erythrocyte Mean Corpuscular Hemoglobin
definition: A quantitative measurement of the mean amount of hemoglobin per erythrocyte in a biological specimen.

label: Erythrocyte Mean Corpuscular Hemoglobin Concentration
definition: A quantitative measurement of the mean amount of hemoglobin per erythrocytes in a specified volume of a biological specimen.

label: Erythrocyte Mean Corpuscular Volume
definition: A quantitative measurement of the mean volume of erythrocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Erythrocyte Distribution Width Measurement
definition: A value derived from mean corpuscular volume and the standard deviation of the red blood cell volume in a whole blood specimen.

label: Dacryocyte Analysis
definition: A count of dacryocytes in unit of a biological specimen.

label: Hypochromia
definition: An observation which indicates that the hemoglobin concentration in a red blood cell specimen has fallen below a specified level.

label: Polychromasia
definition: A measurement of the blue-staining characteristic of newly generated erythrocytes.

label: International Normalized Ratio of Prothrombin Time
pref_label: International Normalized Ratio of Prothrombin Time
definition: A ratio that represents the prothrombin time for a plasma specimen, divided by the result for a control plasma specimen, further standardized for the International Sensitivity Index of the tissue factor (thromboplastin) used in the test.

label: Serum VLDL Cholesterol Measurement
definition: A measurement of the very low density lipoprotein cholesterol in a biological specimen.

label: Triacylglycerol Lipase Measurement
definition: A measurement of the pancreatic lipase in a biological specimen.

label: Sodium Measurement
definition: A measurement of the sodium in a biological specimen.

label: Nitrite Measurement
definition: A measurement of the nitrite in a urine specimen.

label: Triglyceride Measurement
definition: A measurement of the triglycerides in a biological specimen.

label: Thyrotropin Measurement
definition: A measurement of the thyrotropin in a biological specimen.

label: Urate Measurement
definition: A measurement of the urate in a biological specimen.

label: Urea Measurement
definition: A measurement of the urea in a biological specimen.

label: Urobilinogen Measurement
definition: A measurement of the urobilinogen in a biological specimen.

label: Vitamin B12 Measurement
definition: A measurement of the Vitamin B12 in a serum specimen.

label: Atypical Lymphocyte Count
definition: A count of the atypical lymphocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Atypical Lymphocyte To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of the atypical lymphocytes to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Lymphocyte To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of the lymphocytes to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Macrocyte Count
definition: A count of the macrocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Microcyte Count
definition: A count of the microcytes per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Monocyte Count
definition: A count of the monocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Monocyte To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of the monocytes to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Myeloblast To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of the myeloblasts to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Myelocyte To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of the myelocytes to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Neutrophil To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: The determination of the ratio of neutrophils compared to leukocytes in a blood sample. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

label: Reticulocyte To Erythrocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of reticulocytes to erythrocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Prolymphocyte To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of prolymphocytes to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Neutrophil Band Form Count
definition: A count of the banded neutrophils per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Neutrophil Band Form To Leukocyte Ratio
pref_label: Neutrophil Band Form To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of the banded neutrophils to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Specific Gravity
definition: A ratio of the density of a fluid to the density of water.

label: Magnesium Measurement
definition: A measurement of the magnesium in a biological specimen.

label: Gamma Glutamyl Transpeptidase Measurement
definition: A measurement of the gamma glutamyl transpeptidase in a biological specimen.

label: Hemoglobin Measurement
definition: A measurement of the hemoglobin in a biological specimen.

label: Glycosylated Hemoglobin Measurement
definition: A measurement of the glycosylated hemoglobin in a biological specimen.

label: Hepatitis B Virus Surface Antigen Measurement
pref_label: Hepatitis B Virus Surface Antigen Measurement
definition: A measurement of the surface antigen reaction of a biological specimen to the Hepatitis B virus.

label: Choriogonadotropin Beta Measurement
definition: A measurement of the Choriogonadotropin Beta in a biological specimen.

label: Potassium Measurement
definition: A measurement of the potassium in a biological specimen.

label: Ketone Measurement
definition: A measurement of the ketones in a biological specimen.

label: Lactate Dehydrogenase Measurement
definition: A measurement of the lactate dehydrogenase in a biological specimen.

label: Leukocyte Esterase Measurement
definition: A measurement of the enzyme which indicates the presence of white blood cells in a biological specimen.

label: Phosphate Measurement
definition: A measurement of the phosphate in a biological specimen.

label: Total Protein Measurement
definition: A measurement of a group of complex organic macromolecules composed of one or more alpha-L-amino acid chains in a biological specimen.

label: Laboratory Test Name
pref_label: CDISC SDTM Laboratory Test Terminology by Name
definition: Terminology used for Laboratory Tests of the CDISC Standard Data Tabulation Model.

label: Anisocytosis
definition: A measurement of the inequality in the size of the red blood cells in a whole blood specimen.

label: Poikilocytosis
definition: A measurement of the odd-shaped erythrocytes in a whole blood specimen.

label: Total Bilirubin
definition: A measurement of the total bilirubin in a biological specimen.

label: Partial Thromboplastin Time
definition: A measurement of the length of time that it takes for clotting to occur when reagents are added to a plasma specimen. The test is partial due to the absence of tissue factor (Factor III) from the reaction mixture.

label: Plasma Glucose Measurement
definition: A measurement of the glucose in a biological specimen.

label: pH
definition: A measure of the acidity or alkalinity of a fluid on a scale of 0 to 14.

label: Erythrocyte Count
definition: A count of the total erythrocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Reticulocyte Count
definition: A count of the reticulocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Leukocyte Count
definition: A count of the leukocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Lymphocyte Count
definition: A count of the lymphocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Platelet Count
definition: A count of the platelets per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Blood Urea Nitrogen Measurement
definition: A measurement of the urea nitrogen in a blood specimen.

label: Serum Total Cholesterol Measurement
definition: A measurement of the cholesterol in a biological specimen.

label: Serum HDL Cholesterol Measurement
definition: A measurement of the high density lipoprotein cholesterol in a biological specimen.

label: Serum LDL Cholesterol Measurement
definition: A measurement of the low density lipoprotein cholesterol in a biological specimen.

label: Prothrombin Time
definition: A blood clotting measurement that evaluates the extrinsic pathway of coagulation and is expressed in units of time or percent activity.

label: Absolute Neutrophil Count
definition: A count of the neutrophils per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Albumin Measurement
definition: A measurement of the albumin protein in a biological specimen.

label: Alkaline Phosphatase Measurement
definition: A measurement of the alkaline phosphatase in a biological specimen.

label: Alanine Aminotransferase Measurement
definition: A measurement of the alanine aminotransferase in a biological specimen.

label: Amylase Measurement
definition: A measurement of the pancreatic enzyme amylase in a biological specimen.

label: Aspartate Aminotransferase Measurement
definition: A measurement of the aspartate aminotransferase in a biological specimen.

label: Bacterial Count
definition: A measurement of the bacteria in a biological specimen.

label: Total Basophil Count
definition: A count of the basophils per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Basophil To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of the basophils to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Direct Bilirubin Measurement
definition: A measurement of the conjugated or water-soluble bilirubin in a biological specimen.

label: Indirect Bilirubin Measurement
definition: A measurement of the unconjugated or non-water-soluble bilirubin in a biological specimen.

label: Blast To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of the blasts to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Calcium Measurement
definition: A measurement of the calcium in a biological specimen.

label: Creatine Kinase Measurement
definition: A measurement of the total creatine kinase in a biological specimen.

label: Creatine Kinase BB Measurement
definition: A measurement of the homozygous B-type creatine kinase in a biological specimen.

label: Creatine Kinase MB Measurement
definition: A measurement of the heterozygous MB-type creatine kinase in a biological specimen.

label: Creatine Kinase MM Measurement
definition: A measurement of the homozygous M-type creatine kinase in a biological specimen.

label: Chloride Measurement
definition: A measurement of the chloride in a biological specimen.

label: Carbon Dioxide Measurement
definition: A measurement of the carbon dioxide gas in a biological specimen.

label: Color Assessment
definition: A measurement of the color of a biological specimen.

label: Creatinine Measurement
definition: A measurement of the creatinine in a biological specimen.

label: C-Reactive Protein Measurement
definition: A measurement of the C reactive protein in a biological specimen.

label: Elliptocyte Count
definition: A count of the elliptocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Eosinophil Count
definition: A count of the eosinophils per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Eosinophil To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of the eosinophils to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Epithelial Cell Count
definition: A measurement of the epithelial cells in a biological specimen.

label: Fibrinogen Measurement
definition: A measurement of the fibrinogen in a biological specimen.

label: Hematocrit
definition: The percentage of a whole blood specimen that is composed of red blood cells (erythrocytes).

label: Erythrocyte Mean Corpuscular Hemoglobin
definition: A quantitative measurement of the mean amount of hemoglobin per erythrocyte in a biological specimen.

label: Erythrocyte Mean Corpuscular Hemoglobin Concentration
definition: A quantitative measurement of the mean amount of hemoglobin per erythrocytes in a specified volume of a biological specimen.

label: Erythrocyte Mean Corpuscular Volume
definition: A quantitative measurement of the mean volume of erythrocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Erythrocyte Distribution Width Measurement
definition: A value derived from mean corpuscular volume and the standard deviation of the red blood cell volume in a whole blood specimen.

label: Dacryocyte Analysis
definition: A count of dacryocytes in unit of a biological specimen.

label: Hypochromia
definition: An observation which indicates that the hemoglobin concentration in a red blood cell specimen has fallen below a specified level.

label: Polychromasia
definition: A measurement of the blue-staining characteristic of newly generated erythrocytes.

label: International Normalized Ratio of Prothrombin Time
pref_label: International Normalized Ratio of Prothrombin Time
definition: A ratio that represents the prothrombin time for a plasma specimen, divided by the result for a control plasma specimen, further standardized for the International Sensitivity Index of the tissue factor (thromboplastin) used in the test.

label: Serum VLDL Cholesterol Measurement
definition: A measurement of the very low density lipoprotein cholesterol in a biological specimen.

label: Triacylglycerol Lipase Measurement
definition: A measurement of the pancreatic lipase in a biological specimen.

label: Sodium Measurement
definition: A measurement of the sodium in a biological specimen.

label: Nitrite Measurement
definition: A measurement of the nitrite in a urine specimen.

label: Triglyceride Measurement
definition: A measurement of the triglycerides in a biological specimen.

label: Thyrotropin Measurement
definition: A measurement of the thyrotropin in a biological specimen.

label: Urate Measurement
definition: A measurement of the urate in a biological specimen.

label: Urea Measurement
definition: A measurement of the urea in a biological specimen.

label: Urobilinogen Measurement
definition: A measurement of the urobilinogen in a biological specimen.

label: Vitamin B12 Measurement
definition: A measurement of the Vitamin B12 in a serum specimen.

label: Atypical Lymphocyte Count
definition: A count of the atypical lymphocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Atypical Lymphocyte To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of the atypical lymphocytes to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Lymphocyte To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of the lymphocytes to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Macrocyte Count
definition: A count of the macrocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Microcyte Count
definition: A count of the microcytes per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Monocyte Count
definition: A count of the monocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Monocyte To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of the monocytes to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Myeloblast To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of the myeloblasts to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Myelocyte To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of the myelocytes to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Neutrophil To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: The determination of the ratio of neutrophils compared to leukocytes in a blood sample. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

label: Reticulocyte To Erythrocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of reticulocytes to erythrocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Prolymphocyte To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of prolymphocytes to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Neutrophil Band Form Count
definition: A count of the banded neutrophils per unit of a biological specimen.

label: Neutrophil Band Form To Leukocyte Ratio
pref_label: Neutrophil Band Form To Leukocyte Ratio
definition: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of the banded neutrophils to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

label: Specific Gravity
definition: A ratio of the density of a fluid to the density of water.

label: Magnesium Measurement
definition: A measurement of the magnesium in a biological specimen.

label: Gamma Glutamyl Transpeptidase Measurement
definition: A measurement of the gamma glutamyl transpeptidase in a biological specimen.

label: Hemoglobin Measurement
definition: A measurement of the hemoglobin in a biological specimen.

label: Glycosylated Hemoglobin Measurement
definition: A measurement of the glycosylated hemoglobin in a biological specimen.

label: Hepatitis B Virus Surface Antigen Measurement
pref_label: Hepatitis B Virus Surface Antigen Measurement
definition: A measurement of the surface antigen reaction of a biological specimen to the Hepatitis B virus.

label: Choriogonadotropin Beta Measurement
definition: A measurement of the Choriogonadotropin Beta in a biological specimen.

label: Potassium Measurement
definition: A measurement of the potassium in a biological specimen.

label: Ketone Measurement
definition: A measurement of the ketones in a biological specimen.

label: Lactate Dehydrogenase Measurement
definition: A measurement of the lactate dehydrogenase in a biological specimen.

label: Leukocyte Esterase Measurement
definition: A measurement of the enzyme which indicates the presence of white blood cells in a biological specimen.

label: Phosphate Measurement
definition: A measurement of the phosphate in a biological specimen.

label: Total Protein Measurement
definition: A measurement of a group of complex organic macromolecules composed of one or more alpha-L-amino acid chains in a biological specimen.

label: Action Taken with Study Treatment
pref_label: CDISC SDTM Action Taken with Study Treatment Terminology
definition: The reason that changes were made to the therapy under study. (NCI)

label: Dose Increased
definition: An indication that a medication schedule was modified by addition; either by changing the frequency, strength or amount. (NCI)

label: Dose Not Changed
definition: An indication that a medication schedule was maintained. (NCI)

label: Dose Reduced
definition: An indication that a medication schedule was modified by subtraction, either by changing the frequency, strength or amount. (NCI)

label: Drug Interrupted
definition: An indication that a medication schedule was modified by temporarily terminating a prescribed regimen of medication. (NCI)

label: Drug Withdrawn
definition: An indication that a medication schedule was modified through termination of a prescribed regimen of medication. (NCI)

label: Not Applicable
definition: Determination of a value is not relevant in the current context. (NCI)

label: Unknown
definition: Not known, not observed, not recorded, or refused. (NCI)

label: Outcome of Event
pref_label: CDISC SDTM Adverse Event Outcome Terminology
definition: A condition or event that is attributed to the adverse event and is the result or conclusion of the adverse event. (NCI)

label: Death Related to Adverse Event
definition: The termination of life as a result of an adverse event. (NCI)

label: Not Recovered or Not Resolved
definition: One of the possible results of an adverse event outcome that indicates that the event has not improved or recuperated. (NCI)

label: Recovered or Resolved
definition: One of the possible results of an adverse event outcome that indicates that the event has improved or recuperated. (NCI)

label: Recovered or Resolved with Sequelae
definition: One of the possible results of an adverse event outcome where the subject recuperated but retained pathological conditions resulting from the prior disease or injury. (NCI)

label: Recovering or Resolving
definition: One of the possible results of an adverse event outcome that indicates that the event is improving. (NCI)

label: Unknown
definition: Not known, not observed, not recorded, or refused. (NCI)

label: Age Span
definition: Subgroups of populations based on age. (NCI)

label: Adolescent
definition: A juvenile between the onset of puberty and maturity; in the state of development between puberty and maturity. (NCI)

label: Adult 18-65 Years Old
definition: A person from 18 years to 65 years of age. (NCI)

label: Children 2-11 Years Old
definition: A person from 2 years to 11 years of age. (NCI)

label: Elderly
definition: An age group comprised by people 65 years of age and older. (NCI)

label: In Utero
definition: The period of time during which the embryo or foetus is present in the uterus of the female. Also describes the location of the embryo or foetus as being in the uterus in contrast to outside the uterus (ex utero). (NCI)

label: Infant And Toddler
definition: A person from 28 days to 23 months of age. (NCI)

label: Newborn
definition: An infant during the first month after birth. (NCI)

label: Preterm Newborn Infant
definition: An infant born prior to completion of the normal gestation period. (NCI)

label: Age Unit
definition: Those units of time that are routinely used to express the age of a person. (NCI)

label: Day
definition: The time for Earth to make a complete rotation on its axis; ordinarily divided into twenty-four hours.  This also refers to a specific day. (NCI)

label: Hour
definition: A unit measure of time equal to 3,600 seconds or 60 minutes. It is approximately 1/24 of a median day. (NCI)

label: Month
definition: One of the 12 divisions of a year as determined by a calendar.  It corresponds to the unit of time of approximately to one cycle of the moon's phases, about 30 days or 4 weeks. (NCI)

label: Week
definition: Any period of seven consecutive days. (NCI)

label: Year
definition: The period of time that it takes for Earth to make a complete revolution around the sun, approximately 365 days; a specific one year period. (NCI)

label: Category for Inclusion/Exclusion
pref_label: CDISC SDTM Category of Inclusion And Or ExclusionTerminology
definition: A collection of criteria on which subjects are evaluated and that must be met by all study subjects. (NCI)

label: Exclusion
definition: List of characteristics in a protocol, any one of which may exclude a potential subject from participation in a study. (CDISC glossary)

label: Inclusion
definition: The criteria in a protocol that prospective subjects must meet to be eligible for participation in a study.  NOTE: Exclusion and inclusion criteria define the study population. See also exclusion criteria. (CDISC glossary)

label: CDISC System Organ Class
pref_label: CDISC SDTM System Organ Class Terminology
definition: Terms at the highest level of the CDISC system organ class terminology.

label: Hematopoietic and Lymphoid System Disorder
definition: Any deviation from the normal structure or function of the blood or lymphatic system that is manifested by a characteristic set of symptoms and signs. (NCI)

label: Heart Disorder
definition: Any deviation from the normal structure or function of the cardiac system that is manifested by a characteristic set of symptoms and signs. (NCI)

label: Congenital, Familial and Genetic Disorder Class
pref_label: Congenital, Familial and Genetic Disorder Class
definition: A class of disorders that encompasses conditions resulting from a congenital, familial hereditary trait or genetic abnormality as is manifested by a characterstic set of symptoms and signs. (NCI)

label: Ear and Labyrinth Disorder Class
definition: Any deviation from the normal structure or function of the ear or labyrinth that is manifested by a characteristic set of symptoms and signs. (NCI)

label: Endocrine Disorder
definition: Any deviation from the normal structure or function of the endocrine system that is manifested by a characteristic set of symptoms and signs. (NCI)

label: Eye Disorder
definition: Any deviation from the normal structure or function of the eye that is manifested by a characteristic set of symptoms and signs. (NCI)

label: Gastrointestinal Disorder
definition: Diseases of the digestive tract (oral cavity to anus) and associated organs (salivary glands, liver, pancreas). (NCI)

label: General Disorders and Administration Site Conditions Class
notation: GENERAL DISORDERS AND ADMINISTRATION SITE CONDITIONS
pref_label: General Disorders and Administration Site Conditions Class
definition: A class of disorders that encompasses conditions of a general kind that result from a disease, the treatment of disease or administration of treatment at a particular site and are manifested by a characteristic set of symptoms and signs. (NCI)

label: Liver and Biliary Tract Disorder
definition: Any deviation from the normal structure or function of the liver or biliary tract that is manifested by a characteristic set of symptoms and signs. (NCI)

label: Immune System Disorder
definition: A disorder resulting from an abnormality in the immune system. -- 2003 (NCI)

label: Infectious Disorder
definition: A disorder resulting from the presence and activity of a microbial, viral, or parasitic agent. It can be transmitted by direct or indirect contact. -- 2003 (NCI)

label: Injury, Poisoning and Procedural Complication Class
pref_label: Injury, Poisoning and Procedural Complication Class
definition: A class of disorders that encompasses conditions resulting from an injury, poisoning or procedure. (NCI)

label: Investigation
definition: The act or process of a systematic and thorough examination; research, study; the process of inquiring into or following up, intended to develop facts. (NCI)

label: Metabolism and Nutrition Disorder Class
definition: A class of disorders that encompasses conditions occurring as a result of metabolic dysfunction or deviation from the normal nutritional requirements. (NCI)

label: Connective and Soft Tissue Disorder
definition: Any deviation from the normal structure or function of the musculoskeletal or connective tissue that is manifested by a characteristic set of symptoms and signs. (NCI)

label: Neoplasm
notation: NEOPLASMS BENIGN, MALIGNANT AND UNSPECIFIED (INCL CYSTS AND POLYPS)
definition: An abnormal tissue growth resulted from uncontrolled cell proliferation.  Benign neoplastic cells resemble normal cells without exhibiting significant cytologic atypia, while malignant ones exhibit overt signs such as dysplastic features, atypical mitotic figures, necrosis, nuclear pleomorphism, and anaplasia.  Representative examples of benign neoplasms include papillomas, cystadenomas, and lipomas; malignant neoplasms include carcinomas, sarcomas, lymphomas, and leukemias. -- 2004 (NCI)

label: Nervous System Disorder
definition: Any deviation from the normal structure or function of the nervous system that is manifested by a characteristic set of symptoms and signs. (NCI)

label: Pregnancy, Puerperium and Perinatal Condition Class
pref_label: Pregnancy, Puerperium and Perinatal Condition Class
definition: A class of conditions associated with pregnancy, puerperium and perinatal status. (NCI)

label: Psychiatric Disorder
definition: Any deviation from the normal structure or function of the brain and a psychiatric condition, that results in an impairment of an individual's normal cognitive, emotional, or behavioral functioning, and is caused by physiological or psychosocial factors. (NCI)

label: Urinary System Disorder
definition: Disorders of any part of the urologic system. (NCI)

label: Reproductive System and Breast Disorder Class
pref_label: Reproductive System and Breast Disorder Class
definition: Any deviation from the normal structure or function of the reproductive system or breast that is manifested by a characteristic set of symptoms and signs. (NCI)

label: Respiratory and Thoracic Disorder
definition: Any deviation from the normal structure or function of the respiratory system including the thorax and mediastinum that is manifested by a characteristic set of symptoms and signs. (NCI)

label: Skin Disorder
definition: Any deviation from the normal structure or function of the skin or subcutaneous tissue that is manifested by a characteristic set of symptoms and signs.(NCI)

label: Social Circumstances
definition: A set of concepts that results from or is influenced by criteria or activities associated with the social environment of a person. (NCI)

label: Procedure
definition: A particular course of action intended to achieve a result. (NCI)

label: Vascular Disorder
definition: Any deviation from the normal structure or function of the vascular system that is manifested by a characteristic set of symptoms and signs. (NCI)

label: Common Terminology Criteria for Adverse Events
pref_label: CDISC SDTM CommonTerminology Criteria for Adverse Event Grade Terminology
definition: A standard terminology developed to report adverse events occurring in cancer clinical trials.  Common terminology criteria for adverse events (CTCAE) are used in study adverse event summaries and Investigational New Drug reports to the Food and Drug Administration.  The CTCAE contain a grading scale for each adverse event term representing the severity of the event. (NCI)

label: Mild Adverse Event
definition: A type of adverse event that is usually transient and may require only minimal treatment or therapeutic intervention. The event does not generally interfere with usual activities of daily living.

label: Moderate Adverse Event
definition: A type of adverse event that is usually alleviated with additional specific therapeutic intervention. The event interferes with usual activities of daily living, causing discomfort but poses no significant or permanent risk of harm to the research participant.

label: Severe Adverse Event
definition: A type of adverse event that requires intensive therapeutic intervention. The event interrupts usual activities of daily living, or significantly affects clinical status. The event possesses a significant risk of harm to the research participant and hospitalization may be required.

label: Life Threatening or Disabling Adverse Event
pref_label: Life Threatening or Disabling Adverse Event
definition: An adverse event, and/or its immediate sequelae, which is associated with an imminent risk of death or which is associated with physical or mental disabilities that affect or limit the ability of a person to perform activities of daily living (eating, ambulation, toileting, etc.) See NCI Common Terminology Criteria for Adverse Events.

label: Death Related to Adverse Event
definition: The termination of life as a result of an adverse event. (NCI)

label: Control Type
definition: Comparator against which the study treatment is evaluated (e.g., concurrent (placebo, no treatment, dose-response, active), external (historical, published literature).

label: Active Control
definition: A type of control, which has a demonstrated effect, administered as a comparator, to subjects in a clinical trial. [From ICH E10].

label: None
definition: No person or thing, nobody, not any. (NCI)

label: Placebo Control
definition: Use of an inactive compound identical in appearance to drug or treatment being tested in experimental research, which may or may not be known to the physician and/or subject, administered to distinguish between drug action and suggestive effect of the drug or treatment under study. The effects of the active drug or treatment are compared to the effects of the placebo. (NCI)

label: Country
definition: A collective generic term that refers here to a wide variety of dependencies, areas of special sovereignty, uninhabited islands, and other entities in addition to the traditional countries or independent states. (NCI)

label: Aruba
definition: Island in the Caribbean Sea, north of Venezuela.

label: Afghanistan
definition: A country in Southern Asia, north and west of Pakistan, east of Iran.

label: Angola
definition: A country in Southern Africa, bordering the South Atlantic Ocean, between Namibia and Democratic Republic of the Congo.

label: Anguilla
definition: An island in the Caribbean Sea, east of Puerto Rico.

label: Aland Islands
definition: An archipelago in the Baltic Sea at the entrance to the Gulf of Bothnia between Sweden and Finland.

label: Albania
definition: A country in Southeastern Europe, bordering the Adriatic Sea and Ionian Sea, between Greece and Serbia and Montenegro.

label: Andorra
definition: A country in Southwestern Europe, between France and Spain.

label: Netherlands Antilles
definition: A country in the Caribbean, comprising two island groups in the Caribbean Sea - one includes Curacao and Bonaire north of Venezuela; the other is east of the Virgin Islands.

label: United Arab Emirates
definition: A country in the Middle East, bordering the Gulf of Oman and the Persian Gulf, between Oman and Saudi Arabia.

label: Argentina
definition: A country in Southern South America, bordering the South Atlantic Ocean, between Chile and Uruguay.

label: Armenia
definition: A country in Southwestern Asia, east of Turkey.

label: American Samoa
definition: A group of islands in the South Pacific Ocean, about half way between Hawaii and New Zealand.

label: Antarctica
definition: The continent lying mostly south of the Antarctic Circle.

label: French Southern Territories
definition: Islands in the southern Indian Ocean, south of Africa, about equidistant between Africa, Antarctica, and Australia.

label: Antigua and Barbuda
definition: Islands between the Caribbean Sea and the North Atlantic Ocean, east-southeast of Puerto Rico.

label: Australia
definition: The continent between the Indian Ocean and the South Pacific Ocean.

label: Austria
definition: A country in Central Europe, north of Italy and Slovenia.

label: Azerbaijan
definition: A country in Southwestern Asia, bordering the Caspian Sea, between Iran and Russia.

label: Burundi
definition: A country in Central Africa, east of Democratic Republic of the Congo.

label: Belgium
definition: A country in Western Europe, bordering the North Sea, between France and the Netherlands.

label: Benin Republic
definition: A country in Western Africa, bordering the North Atlantic Ocean, between Nigeria and Togo.

label: Burkina Faso
definition: A country in Western Africa, north of Ghana.

label: Bangladesh
definition: A country in Southern Asia, bordering the Bay of Bengal, between Burma and India.

label: Bulgaria
definition: A country in Southeastern Europe, bordering the Black Sea, between Romania and Turkey.

label: Bahrain
definition: An archipelago in the Persian Gulf, east of Saudi Arabia.

label: Bahamas
definition: A chain of islands in the North Atlantic Ocean, southeast of Florida.

label: Bosnia-Herzegovina
definition: A country in Southeastern Europe, bordering the Adriatic Sea and Croatia.

label: Belarus
definition: A country in Eastern Europe, east of Poland.

label: Belize
definition: A country in Central America, bordering the Caribbean Sea, between Guatemala and Mexico.

label: Bermuda
definition: No Definition

label: Bolivia
definition: A country in Central South America, southwest of Brazil.

label: Brazil
definition: A country in Eastern South America, bordering the Atlantic Ocean.

label: Barbados
definition: An island between the Caribbean Sea and the North Atlantic Ocean, northeast of Venezuela.

label: Brunei Darussalam
definition: A country in Southeastern Asia, bordering the South China Sea and Malaysia.

label: Bhutan
definition: A country in Southern Asia, between China and India.

label: Bouvet Island
definition: An island in the South Atlantic Ocean, south-southwest of the Cape of Good Hope (South Africa).

label: Botswana
definition: A country in Southern Africa, north of South Africa.

label: Central African Republic
definition: A country in Central Africa, north of Democratic Republic of the Congo.

label: Canada
definition: A country in Northern North America, bordering the North Atlantic Ocean on the east, North Pacific Ocean on the west, and the Arctic Ocean on the north, north of the conterminous US.

label: Cocos (Keeling) Islands
definition: A group of islands in the Indian Ocean, south of Indonesia, about halfway from Australia to Sri Lanka.

label: Switzerland
definition: A country in Central Europe, east of France, north of Italy.

label: Chile
definition: A country in Southern South America, bordering the South Atlantic Ocean and South Pacific Ocean, between Argentina and Peru.

label: China
definition: A country in Eastern Asia, bordering the East China Sea, Korea Bay, Yellow Sea, and South China Sea, between North Korea and Vietnam.

label: Cote d'Ivoire
definition: A country in Western Africa, bordering the North Atlantic Ocean, between Ghana and Liberia.

label: Cameroon
definition: A country in Western Africa, bordering the Bight of Biafra, between Equatorial Guinea and Nigeria.

label: Democratic Republic of the Congo
definition: A country in Central Africa, northeast of Angola.

label: Congo
definition: A country in Western Africa, bordering the South Atlantic Ocean, between Angola and Gabon.

label: Cook Islands
definition: A group of islands in the South Pacific Ocean, about one-half of the way from Hawaii to New Zealand.

label: Colombia
definition: A country in Northern South America, bordering the Caribbean Sea, between Panama and Venezuela, and bordering the North Pacific Ocean, between Ecuador and Panama.

label: Comoros
definition: A group of islands in the Mozambique Channel, about two-thirds of the way between northern Madagascar and northern Mozambique.

label: Cape Verde
definition: A group of islands in the North Atlantic Ocean, west of Senegal.

label: Costa Rica
definition: A country in Central America, bordering both the Caribbean Sea and the North Pacific Ocean, between Nicaragua and Panama.

label: Cuba
definition: An island between the Caribbean Sea and the North Atlantic Ocean, 150 km south of Key West, Florida.

label: Christmas Island
definition: An Australian-administered island in the eastern Indian Ocean south of Java, Indonesia.

label: Cayman Islands
definition: An island group in the Caribbean Sea, nearly one-half of the way from Cuba to Honduras.

label: Cyprus
definition: An island in the Mediterranean Sea, south of Turkey.

label: Czech Republic
definition: A country in Central Europe, southeast of Germany.

label: Germany
definition: A country in Central Europe, bordering the Baltic Sea and the North Sea, between the Netherlands and Poland, south of Denmark.

label: Djibouti
definition: A country in Eastern Africa, bordering the Gulf of Aden and the Red Sea, between Eritrea and Somalia.

label: Dominica
definition: An island between the Caribbean Sea and the North Atlantic Ocean, about one-half of the way from Puerto Rico to Trinidad and Tobago.

label: Denmark
definition: A country in Northern Europe, bordering the Baltic Sea and the North Sea, on a peninsula north of Germany (Jutland); also includes two major islands (Sjaelland and Fyn).

label: Dominican Republic
definition: A country comprising the eastern two-thirds of the island of Hispaniola, between the Caribbean Sea and the North Atlantic Ocean, east of Haiti.

label: Algeria
definition: A country in Northern Africa, bordering the Mediterranean Sea, between Morocco and Tunisia.

label: Ecuador
definition: A country in Western South America, bordering the Pacific Ocean at the Equator, between Colombia and Peru.

label: Egypt
definition: A country in Northern Africa, bordering the Mediterranean Sea, between Libya and the Gaza Strip.

label: Eritrea
definition: A country in Eastern Africa, bordering the Red Sea, between Djibouti and Sudan.

label: Western Sahara
definition: A country in Northern Africa, bordering the North Atlantic Ocean, between Mauritania and Morocco.

label: Spain
definition: A country in Southwestern Europe, bordering the Bay of Biscay, Mediterranean Sea, North Atlantic Ocean, and Pyrenees Mountains, southwest of France.

label: Estonia
definition: A country in Eastern Europe, bordering the Baltic Sea and Gulf of Finland, between Latvia and Russia.

label: Ethiopia
definition: A country in Eastern Africa, west of Somalia.

label: Finland
definition: A country in Northern Europe, bordering the Baltic Sea, Gulf of Bothnia, and Gulf of Finland, between Sweden and Russia.

label: Fiji
definition: An island group in the South Pacific Ocean, about two-thirds of the way from Hawaii to New Zealand.

label: Falkland Islands
definition: Islands in the South Atlantic Ocean, east of southern Argentina.

label: France
definition: A country in Western Europe, bordering the Bay of Biscay and English Channel, between Belgium and Spain, southeast of the UK; bordering the Mediterranean Sea, between Italy and Spain.

label: Faroe Islands
definition: An island group between the Norwegian Sea and the North Atlantic Ocean, about one-half of the way from Iceland to Norway.

label: Federated States of Micronesia
definition: An island group in the North Pacific Ocean, about three-quarters of the way from Hawaii to Indonesia.

label: Gabon
definition: A country in Western Africa, bordering the Atlantic Ocean at the Equator, between Republic of the Congo and Equatorial Guinea.

label: United Kingdom

label: Diagnosis Group
definition: A grouping of individuals on the basis of a shared procedure or disease, or lack thereof (e.g. healthy volunteers, type 2 diabetic subjects, subjects with renal cell cancer).  Standardized naming systems are available that define the groups within which a subject should be placed. (NCI)

label: Healthy Subject
definition: An individual who is or becomes a participant in a research study and has no significant health-related issues.  (NCI)

label: Dictionary Name
definition: A name given to a reference source that lists words and gives their meaning. (NCI)

label: Thesaurus of Adverse Reaction Term Coding Symbols
alt_label: ['Coding Symbols for a Thesaurus of Adverse Reaction Terms']
pref_label: Thesaurus of Adverse Reaction Term Coding Symbols
definition: A terminology developed and used by the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) for the coding, filing and retrieving of post marketing adverse reaction reports. (NCI)

label: International Classification of Diseases
definition: A system of categories to which morbid entries are assigned according to established criteria. Included is the entire range of conditions in a manageable number of categories, grouped to facilitate mortality reporting. It is produced by the World Health Organization (from ICD-10, p1). The Clinical Modifications, produced by the United States Dept. of Health and Human Services, are larger extensions used for morbidity and general epidemiological purposes, primarily in the U.S. (MSH2005_2004_10_12)

label: Logical Observation Identifiers Names and Codes
pref_label: Logical Observation Identifiers Names and Codes
definition: Published by the The Regenstrief Institute, the Logical Observation Identifiers Names and Codes covers clinical and clinical laboratory terminology. (NCI)

label: MedDRA
definition: MedDRA is an international medical terminology designed to support the classification, retrieval, presentation, and communication of medical information throughout the medical product regulatory cycle. MedDRA was developed under the auspices of the International Conference on Harmonisation of Technical Requirements for Registration of Pharmaceuticals for Human Use (ICH). The MedDRA Maintenance and Support Services Organization (MSSO) holds a contract with the International Federation of Pharmaceutical Manufacturers Associations (IFPMA) to maintain and support the implementation of the terminology. (NCI)

label: Systematized Nomenclature of Medicine
definition: A multiaxial, hierarchical classification system for diseases in man developed by the College of American Pathologists. (NCI)

label: World Health Organization Adverse Reaction Terminology
pref_label: World Health Organization Adverse Reaction Terminology
definition: A terminology implemented by the World Health Organization to describe adverse reactions to a prescribed medication or treatment regimen. (NCI)

label: World Health Organization Drug Dictionary
definition: A reference source of drugs and drug associated information maintained by the World Health Organization. (NCI)

label: Not Done
definition: Indicates a task, process or examination that has either not been initiated or completed. (NCI)

label: Not Done
definition: Indicates a task, process or examination that has either not been initiated or completed. (NCI)

label: Patient Ethnic Group
definition: A social group characterized by a distinctive social and cultural tradition maintained from generation to generation, a common history and origin and a sense of identification with the group; members of the group have distinctive features in their way of life, shared experiences and often a common genetic heritage; these features may be reflected in their experience of health and disease. (NCI)

label: Hispanic or Latino
definition: A person of Mexican, Puerto Rican, Cuban, Central or South American or other Spanish culture or origin, regardless of race.  (NCI)

label: Not Hispanic or Latino
definition: A person not of Cuban, Mexican, Puerto Rican, South or Central American, or other Spanish culture or origin, regardless of race. An arbitrary ethnic classification. (NCI)

label: Not Stated
definition: Not provided or available

label: Unknown
definition: Not known, not observed, not recorded, or refused. (NCI)

label: Pharmaceutical Dosage Form
definition: The form of the completed pharmaceutical product, e.g. tablet, capsule, injection, elixir, suppository. Dosage form can have a significant effect on the onset, duration and intensity of the pharmacological action of a drug. A pharmaceutical dosage form controls the rate at which the drug is released into the biological fluids. This release rate affects its intrinsic absorption pattern and therefore, the bioavailability of the drug.

label: Aerosol Dosage Form
definition: A product that is packaged under pressure and contains therapeutically active ingredients that are released upon activation of an appropriate valve system; it is intended for topical application to the skin as well as local application into the nose (nasal aerosols), mouth (lingual aerosols), or lungs (inhalation aerosols). (FDA)

label: Aerosol Foam Dosage Form
definition: A dosage form containing one or more active ingredients, surfactants, aqueous or non-aqueous liquids, and the propellants; if the propellant is in the internal (discontinuous) phase (i.e., of the oil-in-water type), a stable foam is discharged, and if the propellant is in the external (continuous) phase (i.e., of the water-in-oil type), a spray or a quick-breaking foam is discharged. (FDA)

label: Metered Aerosol Dosage Form
definition: A pressurized dosage form consisting of metered dose valves which allow for the delivery of a uniform quantity of spray upon each activation. (NCI)

label: Powder Aerosol Dosage Form
definition: A product that is packaged under pressure and contains therapeutically active ingredients, in the form of a powder, that are released upon activation of an appropriate valve system. (NCI)

label: Aerosol Spray Dosage Form
definition: An aerosol product which utilizes a compressed gas as the propellant to provide the force necessary to expel the product as a wet spray; it is applicable to solutions of medicinal agents in aqueous solvents. (NCI)

label: Chewable Bar Dosage Form
definition: A solid dosage form usually in the form of a rectangle that is meant to be chewed. (NCI)

label: Bead Dosage Form
definition: A solid dosage form in the shape of a small ball. (NCI)

label: Extended Release Bead Implant Dosage Form
pref_label: Extended Release Bead Implant Dosage Form
definition: A small sterile solid mass consisting of a highly purified drug intended for implantation in the body which would allow at least a reduction in dosing frequency as compared to that drug presented as a conventional dosage form.  (NCI)

label: Block Dosage Form
definition: Solid dosage form, usually in the shape of a square or rectangle. (NCI)

label: Capsule Dosage Form
definition: A solid pharmaceutical dosage form that contains medicinal agent within either a hard or soft soluble container or shell, usually used for the oral administration of medicine. The shells are made of a suitable form of gelatin or other substance. (NCI)

label: Coated Capsule Dosage Form
definition: A solid dosage form in which the drug is enclosed within either a hard or soft soluble container or "shell" made from a suitable form of gelatin; additionally, the capsule is covered in a designated coating. (NCI)

label: Coated Pellets in Capsule Dosage Form
pref_label: Coated Pellets in Capsule Dosage Form
definition: A solid dosage form in which the drug is enclosed within either a hard or soft soluble container or "shell" made from a suitable form of gelatin; the drug itself is in the form of granules to which varying amounts of coating have been applied. (NCI)

label: Extended Release Coated Capsule Dosage Form
pref_label: Extended Release Coated Capsule Dosage Form
definition: A solid dosage form in which the drug is enclosed within either a hard or soft soluble container or "shell" made from a suitable form of gelatin; additionally, the capsule is covered in a designated coating, and which releases a drug (or drugs) in such a manner to allow at least a reduction in dosing frequency as compared to that drug (or drugs) presented as a conventional dosage form. (NCI)

label: Delayed Release Capsule Dosage Form
definition: A solid dosage form in which the drug is enclosed within either a hard or soft soluble container made from a suitable form of gelatin, and which releases a drug (or drugs) at a time other than promptly after administration. Enteric-coated articles are delayed release dosage forms. (NCI)

label: Delayed Release Pellets in Capsule Dosage Form
pref_label: Delayed Release Pellets in Capsule Dosage Form
definition: A solid dosage form in which the drug is enclosed within either a hard or soft soluble container or "shell" made from a suitable form of gelatin; the drug itself is in the form of granules to which enteric coating has been applied, thus delaying release of the drug until its passage into the intestines. (NCI)

label: Extended Release Capsule Dosage Form
definition: A solid dosage form in which the drug is enclosed within either a hard or soft soluble container made from a suitable form of gelatin, and which releases a drug (or drugs) in such a manner to allow a reduction in dosing frequency as compared to that drug (or drugs) presented as a conventional dosage form. (NCI)

label: Extended Release Film Coated Capsule Dosage Form
pref_label: Extended Release Film Coated Capsule Dosage Form
definition: A solid dosage form in which the drug is enclosed within either a hard or soft soluble container or "shell" made from a suitable form of gelatin; additionally, the capsule is covered in a designated film coating, and which releases a drug (or drugs) in such a manner to allow at least a reduction in dosing frequency as compared to that drug (or drugs) presented as a conventional dosage form. (NCI)

label: Gelatin Coated Capsule Dosage Form
definition: A solid dosage form in which the drug is enclosed within either a hard or soft soluble container made from a suitable form of gelatin; through a banding process, the capsule is coated with additional layers of gelatin so as to form a complete seal. (NCI)

label: Liquid Filled Capsule Dosage Form
definition: A solid dosage form in which the drug is enclosed within a soluble, gelatin shell which is plasticized by the addition of a polyol, such as sorbitol or glycerin, and is therefore of a somewhat thicker consistency than that of a hard shell capsule; typically, the active ingredients are dissolved or suspended in a liquid vehicle. (NCI)

label: Cement Dosage Form
definition: A substance that serves to produce solid union between two surfaces. (NCI)

label: Cigarette Dosage Form
definition: A narrow tube filled with material that is capable to burn with release of therapeutically-active substance(s) during the process of smoking. Cigarette is a very efficient drug-delivery inhaler system for fast-acting substances.(FDA)

label: Cloth Dosage Form
definition: A large piece of relatively flat, absorbent material that contains a drug. It is typically used for applying medication or for cleansing. (FDA)

label: Concentrate Dosage Form
definition: A liquid preparation of increased strength and reduced volume which is usually diluted prior to administration. (NCI)

label: Cone Dosage Form
definition: A solid dosage form bounded by a circular base and the surface formed by line segments joining every point of the boundary of the base to a common vertex. A cone (usually containing antibiotics) is normally placed below the gingiva after a dental extraction. (NCI)

label: Extended Release Core Dosage Form
definition: An ocular system placed in the eye from which the drug diffuses through a membrane at a constant rate over a specified period. (NCI)

label: Cream Dosage Form
definition: A semisolid emulsion of either the oil-in-water or the water-in-oil type, ordinarily intended for topical use. (NCI)

label: Augmented Cream Dosage Form
definition: A cream dosage form that enhances drug delivery. Augmentation does not refer to the strength of the drug in the dosage form. NOTE: CDER has decided to refrain from expanding the use of this dosage form due to difficulties in setting specific criteria that must be met to be considered augmented. (FDA)

label: Crystal Dosage Form
definition: A naturally produced angular solid of definite form in which the ultimate units from which it is built up are systematically arranged; they are usually evenly spaced on a regular space lattice.

label: Culture Dosage Form
definition: The propagation of microorganisms or of living tissue cells in special media conducive to their growth. (NCI)

label: Diaphragm Dosage Form
definition: A device usually dome-shaped, worn during copulation over the cervical mouth for prevention of conception or infection. (NCI)

label: Disc Dosage Form
definition: A circular plate-like organ or structure. (FDA)

label: Douche Dosage Form
definition: A liquid preparation, intended for the irrigative cleansing of the vagina, that is prepared from powders, liquid solutions, or liquid concentrates and contains one or more chemical substances dissolved in a suitable solvent or mutually miscible solvents. (NCI)

label: Dressing Dosage Form
definition: The application of various materials for protecting a wound.(FDA)

label: Drug Delivery System
definition: Modern technology, distributed with or as a part of a drug product that allows for the uniform release or targeting of drugs to the body. (FDA)

label: Elixir Dosage Form
definition: A clear, pleasantly flavored, sweetened hydroalcoholic liquid containing dissolved medicinal agents; it is intended for oral use. (NCI)

label: Emulsion Dosage Form
definition: A dosage form consisting of a two-phase system comprised of at least two immiscible liquids (1), one of which is dispersed as droplets (internal or dispersed phase) within the other liquid (external or continuous phase), generally stabilized with one or more emulsifying agents. Note 1: A liquid is pourable; it flows and conforms to its container at room temperature. It displays Newtonian or pseudoplastic flow behavior. Note 2: Emulsion is used as a dosage form term unless a more specific term is applicable, e.g. cream, lotion, ointment. (NCI)

label: Enema Dosage Form
definition: A rectal preparation for therapeutic, diagnostic, or nutritive purposes.  (NCI)

label: Extract Dosage Form
definition: A concentrated preparation of vegetable or animal drugs obtained by removal of the active constituents of the respective drugs with a suitable menstrua, evaporation of all or nearly all of the solvent, and adjustment of the residual masses or powders to the prescribed standards. (NCI)

label: Extended Release Fiber Dosage Form
definition: A slender and elongated solid thread-like substance that delivers drug in such a manner to allow a reduction in dosing frequency as compared to that drug (or drugs) presented as a conventional dosage form. (FDA)

label: Film Dosage Form
definition: A thin layer or coating. (NCI)

label: Extended Release Film Dosage Form
definition: A drug delivery system in the form of a film that releases the drug over an extended period in such a way as to maintain constant drug levels in the blood or target tissue. (NCI)

label: Soluble Film Dosage Form
definition: A thin layer or coating which is susceptible to being dissolved when in contact with a liquid. (NCI)

label: Dosage Form For Solution
definition: A product, usually a solid, intended for solution prior to administration. (FDA)

label: Dosage Form For Suspension
definition: A product, usually a solid, intended for suspension prior to administration. (FDA)

label: Extended Release Dosage Form For Suspension
pref_label: Extended Release Dosage Form For Suspension
definition: A product, usually a solid, intended for suspension prior to administration; once the suspension is administered, the drug will be released at a constant rate over a specified period. (FDA)

label: Gas Dosage Form
definition: Any elastic aeriform fluid in which the molecules are separated from one another and have free paths. (NCI)

label: Gel Dosage Form
definition: A semisolid (1) dosage form that contains a gelling agent to provide stiffness to a solution or a colloidal dispersion (2).  A gel may contain suspended particles. Note 1: A semisolid is not pourable; it does not flow or conform to its container at room temperature.  It does not flow at low shear stress and generally exhibits plastic flow behavior. Note 2: A colloidal dispersion is a system in which particles of colloidal dimension (i.e., typically between 1 nm and 1 micrometer) are distributed uniformly throughout a liquid. (NCI)

label: Dentifrice Gel Dosage Form
definition: A combination of a dentifrice (formulation intended to clean and/or polish the teeth, and which may contain certain additional agents), and a gel. It is used with a toothbrush for the purpose of cleaning and polishing the teeth. (NCI)

label: Metered Gel Dosage Form
definition: A gel preparation, with metered dose valves, which allow for the delivery of a uniform quantity of gel upon each activation. (FDA)

label: Generator Dosage Form
definition: An apparatus for the formation of vapor or gas from a liquid or solid by heat or chemical action. The term GENERATOR also applies to radioactive columns from which radionuclides are provided. (NCI)

label: Globule Dosage Form
definition: Also called pellets or pilules, are made of pure sucrose, lactose, or other polysaccharides. They are formed into small globular masses of various sizes, and are medicated by placing them in a vial and adding the liquid drug attenuation in the proportion not less than one percent (v/w). After shaking, the medicated globules are dried at temperatures not to exceed 40 degrees Centigrade. (NCI)

label: Graft Dosage Form
definition: A slip of skin or of other tissue for implantation. (NCI)

label: Granule Dosage Form
definition: A small particle or grain. (NCI)

label: Delayed Release Granule Dosage Form
definition: A small medicinal particle or grain to which an enteric or other coating has been applied, thus delaying release of the drug until its passage into the intestines. (NCI)

label: Effervescent Granule Dosage Form
definition: A small particle or grain containing a medicinal agent in a dry mixture usually composed of sodium bicarbonate, citric acid, and tartaric acid which, when in contact with water, has the capability to release gas, resulting in effervescence. (NCI)

label: Granule For Solution Dosage Form
definition: A small medicinal particle or grain made available in its more stable dry form, to be reconstituted with solvent just before dispensing; the granules are so prepared to contain not only the medicinal agent, but the colorants, flavorants, and any other desired pharmaceutic ingredient. (NCI)

label: Granule For Suspension Dosage Form
definition: A small medicinal particle or grain made available in its more stable dry form, to be reconstituted with solvent just before dispensing to form a suspension; the granules are so prepared to contain not only the medicinal agent, but the colorants, flavorants, and any other desired pharmaceutic ingredient. (NCI)

label: Extended Release Granule For Suspension Dosage Form
pref_label: Extended Release Granule For Suspension Dosage Form
definition: A small medicinal particle or grain made available in its more stable dry form, to be reconstituted with solvent just before dispensing to form a suspension; the extended release system achieves slow release of the drug over an extended period of time and maintains constant drug levels in the blood or target tissue. (NCI)

label: Gum Dosage Form
definition: A mucilaginous excretion from various plants. (NCI)

label: Chewing Gum Dosage Form
definition: A sweetened and flavored insoluble plastic material of various shapes which when chewed, releases a drug substance into the oral cavity. (NCI)

label: Resin Gum Dosage Form
definition: Natural mixture of gum and resin, usually obtained as exudations from plants. (NCI)

label: Implant Dosage Form
definition: A material containing drug intended to be inserted securely and deeply in a living site for growth, slow release, or formation of an organic union. (NCI)

label: Inhalant Dosage Form
definition: A special class of inhalations consisting of a drug or combination of drugs, that by virtue of their high vapor pressure, can be carried by an air current into the nasal passage where they exert their effect; the container from which the inhalant generally is administered is known as an inhaler. (NCI)

label: Liposomal Injection Dosage Form
definition: An injection, which either consists of or forms liposomes (a lipid bilayer vesicle usually composed of phospholipids which is used to encapsulate an active drug substance). (FDA)

label: Injectable Dosage Form
definition: A sterile preparation intended for parenteral use; five distinct classes of injections exist as defined by the USP. (NCI)

label: Emulsion for Injection Dosage Form
definition: An emulsion consisting of a sterile, pyrogen-free preparation intended to be administered parenterally.(FDA)

label: Injectable Lipid Complex Dosage Form
definition: [definition pending](FDA)

label: Powder For Injectable Solution Dosage Form
pref_label: Powder For Injectable Solution Dosage Form
definition: A sterile preparation intended for reconstitution to form a solution for parenteral use. (NCI)

label: Powder For Injectable Suspension Dosage Form
pref_label: Powder For Injectable Suspension Dosage Form
definition: A sterile preparation intended for reconstitution to form a suspension for parenteral use. (NCI)

label: Powder For Injectable Extended Release Suspension Dosage Form
notation: INJECTION, POWDER, FOR SUSPENSION, EXTENDED RELEASE
pref_label: Powder For Injectable Extended Release Suspension Dosage Form
definition: A dried preparation intended for reconstitution to form a suspension for parenteral use which has been formulated in a manner to allow at least a reduction in dosing frequency as compared to that drug presented as a conventional dosage form (e.g., as a solution).(FDA)

label: Lyophilized Powder For Injectable Liposomal Suspension Dosage Form
notation: INJECTION, POWDER, LYOPHILIZED, FOR LIPOSOMAL SUSPENSION
pref_label: Lyophilized Powder For Injectable Liposomal Suspension Dosage Form
definition: A sterile freeze dried preparation intended for reconstitution for parenteral use which has been formulated in a manner that would allow liposomes (a lipid bilayer vesicle usually composed of phospholipids which is used to encapsulate an active drug substance, either within a lipid bilayer or in an aqueous space) to be formed upon reconstitution. (NCI)

label: Lyophilized Powder For Injectable Solution Dosage Form
pref_label: Lyophilized Powder For Injectable Solution Dosage Form
definition: A dosage form intended for the solution prepared by lyophilization ('freeze drying'), a process which involves the removal of water from products in the frozen state at extremely low pressures; this is intended for subsequent addition of liquid to create a solution that conforms in all respects to the requirements for Injections. (NCI)

label: Lyophilized Powder For Injectable Suspension Dosage Form
pref_label: Lyophilized Powder For Injectable Suspension Dosage Form
definition: A liquid preparation, intended for parenteral use, that contains solids suspended in a suitable fluid medium and conforms in all respects to the requirements for Sterile Suspensions; the medicinal agents intended for the suspension are prepared by lyophilization ("freeze drying"), a process which involves the removal of water from products in the frozen state at extremely low pressures. (NCI)

label: Lyophilized Powder For Extended Release Injectable Suspension Dosage Form
notation: INJECTION, POWDER, LYOPHILIZED, FOR SUSPENSION, EXTENDED RELEASE
pref_label: Lyophilized Powder For Extended Release Injectable Suspension Dosage Form
definition: A sterile freeze dried preparation intended for reconstitution for parenteral use which has been formulated in a manner to allow at least a reduction in dosing frequency as compared to that drug presented as a conventional dosage form (e.g., as a solution). (NCI)

label: Injectable Solution Dosage Form
definition: A liquid preparation containing one or more drug substances dissolved in a suitable solvent or mixture of mutually miscible solvents that is suitable for injection. (NCI)

label: Concentrate for Injectable Solution Dosage Form
pref_label: Concentrate for Injectable Solution Dosage Form
definition: A sterile preparation for parenteral use which, upon the addition of suitable solvents, yields a solution conforming in all respects to the requirements for Injections. (NCI)

label: Injectable Suspension Dosage Form
definition: A liquid preparation, suitable for injection, which consists of solid particles dispersed throughout a liquid phase in which the particles are not soluble. It can also consist of an oil phase dispersed throughout an aqueous phase, or vice-versa. (NCI)

label: Injectable Extended Release Suspension Dosage Form
pref_label: Injectable Extended Release Suspension Dosage Form
definition: A sterile preparation intended for parenteral use which has been formulated in a manner to allow at least a reduction in dosing frequency as compared to that drug presented as a conventional dosage form (e.g., as a solution or a prompt drug-releasing, conventional solid dosage form). (NCI)

label: Injectable Liposomal Suspension Dosage Form
definition: A liquid parenteral pharmaceutical dosage form structured as a multilamellar composition of concentric phospholipid spheres that encapsulate the drug (drug delivery systems) separated by layers of water. Drug release is facilitated and controlled by in vivo erosion of the liposomes. To further increase the in vivo circulation time, liposomes in some preparations are covalently derivatized with PEG to produce PEGylated or stealth liposomes. Covalent attachment of drugs to the outer surface of liposomes can potentially serve as a delayed-release product. (NCI)

label: Injectable Sonicated Suspension Dosage Form
definition: A liquid preparation, suitable for injection, which consists of solid particles dispersed throughout a liquid phase in which the particles are not soluble. In addition, the product is sonicated while a gas is bubbled through the suspension, and this results in the formation of microspheres by the solid particles. (NCI)

label: Insert Dosage Form
definition: A specially formulated and shaped non-encapsulated solid preparation intended to be placed into a non-rectal orifice of the body, where drug is released, generally for localized effects. (FDA)

label: Extended Release Insert Dosage Form
definition: A specially formulated and shaped solid preparation (e.g., ring, tablet, or stick) intended to be placed in the vagina by special inserters, where the medication is released, generally for localized effects; the extended release preparation is designed to allow a reduction in dosing frequency. (NCI)

label: Intrauterine Device Dosage Form
definition: A device inserted and left in the uterus to prevent effective conception. (NCI)

label: Irrigant Dosage Form
definition: A sterile solution intended to bathe or flush open wounds or body cavities; they're used topically, never parenterally. (NCI)

label: Jelly Dosage Form
definition: A class of gels--semisolid systems which consist of suspensions made up of either small inorganic particles or large organic molecules interpenetrated by a liquid--in which the structural coherent matrix contains a high portion of liquid, usually water. (NCI)

label: Kit Dosage Form
definition: A packaged collection of related material. (NCI)

label: Dental Liner Dosage Form
definition: A material applied to the inside of the dental cavity, for protection or insulation of the surface.(FDA)

label: Liniment Dosage Form
definition: A solution or mixture of various substances in oil, alcoholic solutions of soap, or emulsions intended for external application. (NCI)

label: Lipstick Dosage Form
definition: A waxy solid, usually colored cosmetic, in stick form for the lips. (NCI)

label: Liquid Dosage Form
definition: A dosage form consisting of a pure chemical in its liquid state. This dosage form term should not be applied to solutions. Note: A liquid is pourable; it flows and conforms to its container at room temperature.  It displays Newtonian or pseudoplastic flow behavior.(FDA)

label: Extended Release Liquid Dosage Form
definition: A liquid that delivers a drug in such a manner to allow a reduction in dosing frequency as compared to that drug (or drugs) presented as a conventional dosage form. (FDA)

label: Lotion Dosage Form
definition: An emulsion, liquid (1) dosage form. This dosage form is generally for external application to the skin (2). Note 1: A liquid is pourable; it flows and conforms to its container at room temperature.  It displays Newtonian or pseudoplastic flow behavior. Note 2: Previously the definition of a lotion was: The term lotion has been used to categorize many topical suspensions, solutions, and emulsions intended for application to the skin. The current definition of a lotion is restricted to an emulsion. (FDA)

label: Augmented Lotion Dosage Form
definition: A lotion dosage form that enhances drug delivery. Augmentation does not refer to the strength of the drug in the dosage form. NOTE: CDER has decided to refrain from expanding the use of this dosage form due to difficulties in setting specific criteria that must be met to be considered augmented. (FDA)

label: Lotion Shampoo Dosage Form
definition: A lotion dosage form which has a soap or detergent that is usually used to clean the hair and scalp; it is often used as a vehicle for dermatologic agents. (FDA)

label: Lozenge Dosage Form
definition: A solid preparation containing one or more medicaments, usually in a flavored, sweetened base which is intended to dissolve or disintegrate slowly in the mouth. A lollipop is a lozenge on a stick.(FDA)

label: Mouthwash Dosage Form
definition: An aqueous solution which is most often used for its deodorant, refreshing, or antiseptic effect. (NCI)

label: Dosage Form Not Applicable
definition: The use of a dosage form term is not relevant or appropriate. (NCI)

label: Oil Dosage Form
definition: An unctuous, combustible substance which is liquid, or easily liquefiable, on warming, and is soluble in ether but insoluble in water. Such substances, depending on their origin, are classified as animal, mineral, or vegetable oils. (NCI)

label: Ointment Dosage Form
definition: A suspension or emulsion, semisolid (1) dosage form, usually containing < 20% water and volatiles (2) and > 50% hydrocarbons, waxes, or polyols as the vehicle. This dosage form is generally for external application to the skin or mucous membranes. Note 1: A semisolid is not pourable; it does not flow or conform to its container at room temperature. It does not flow at low shear stress and generally exhibits plastic flow behavior. Note 2: Percent water and volatiles are measured by a loss on drying test in which the sample is heated at 105 degrees C until constant weight is achieved. (NCI)

label: Augmented Ointment Dosage Form
definition: An ointment dosage form that enhances drug delivery. Augmentation does not refer to the strength of the drug in the dosage form. NOTE: CDER has decided to refrain from expanding the use of this dosage form due to difficulties in setting specific criteria that must be met to be considered augmented. (FDA)

label: Packing Dosage Form
definition: A material, usually covered by or impregnated with a drug, that is inserted into a body cavity or between the tooth enamel and the gingival margin.(FDA)

label: Paste Dosage Form
definition: A semisolid dosage form, containing a large proportion (20 - 50%) of solids finely dispersed in a fatty vehicle.
